Description of incident: A laptop was stolen from the trunk of an auditor's car. Names, Social Security numbers              and earnings of former employees from 2002 to 2005 were exposed.  The Employment Security Department does not have all of the contact information for those affected and used the media to help notify those whose information was compromised.  The laptop contained unemployment insurance reports for 49 Seattle businesses that were undergoing routine audits by Employment Security between November 2004 and October 2005..
